  },
  {
    q: "Why is CMA cheaper than Champion or Hobart?",
    a: "CMA occupies the mid-range value segment by design — it's the brand Ali Group positions against operators who want Ali Group parts chain and service quality but at entry-level or mid-market pricing, below Champion's flagship tier and well below Hobart's premium tier. You get the same Winston-Salem parts supply, the same Ali Group service discipline, same sister-brand cross-parts availability — at a lower new-equipment price. For an LA SMB restaurant, independent bar, or small catering operation where the dishwasher needs to be reliable without being over-specified, CMA is typically the sensible choice. Our service experience: CMA repairs are straightforward, parts are easy to source, and the units hold up well in 8-to-12-year service windows in typical LA mid-volume operations."
  },
  {
    q: "Are CMA Energy Mizer models eligible for California Energy Commission rebates?",
    a: "Energy Mizer is CMA's ENERGY STAR qualified product line — reduced water consumption per rack and heat-recovery configurations that qualify for California Energy Commission commercial foodservice equipment rebates. Check current rebate status at cec.ca.gov/energy-programs or through your LADWP or Southern California Edison commercial rebate program — rebate amounts and qualifying models change over time. For Energy Mizer installs specifically, keep the ENERGY STAR label data plate photographed during installation; you'll need it for the rebate application. We service Energy Mizer across all Ali-channel configurations and can advise on Energy Mizer-specific maintenance that preserves the ENERGY STAR performance characteristics."
  },
  {
    q: "Do you service CMA in LA bars and restaurants with bar-height undercounter units?",
    a: "Yes — the CMA L-Series (L-1X, L-1X16, L-1X36) and EST Series Glass Washer are the specific undercounter models standard in LA bar cluster operations. Craft cocktail bars in WeHo, sports bars in the Valley, hotel bar programs in DTLA and Santa Monica — most of the CMA installs we service in LA are in this undercounter-in-a-bar category. Bar service has some specific patterns we look for: floor-level condenser loading from spilled liquids, door-latch wear from high cycle counts, fill-solenoid issues from the water-supply pressure drops in older commercial buildings. Monthly cleaning is the real preventive for bar undercounters; we set PM schedules on accounts that want this proactive."
  },
  {
    q: "What does CMA Dishmachines repair cost in LA?",
    a: "$120 flat commercial diagnostic, waived with repair. Typical CMA service ranges: door gasket $140–$260, door switch $140–$220, fill solenoid $200–$340, thermostat $180–$300, rinse-aid or detergent pump $180–$320, drain pump $260–$420, rinse booster element $250–$420, wash pump seal kit $280–$460, wash pump rebuild $400–$640, control board $550–$950, 44-Series conveyor drive $500–$850. Most CMA undercounter and door calls land $280–$600 parts-and-labor; 44-Series conveyor jobs run $500–$1,000. CMA pricing typically runs 10–20% below equivalent Champion or Hobart jobs on the same repair category."
  }
];

