  <section class="section">
    <div class="wrap narrow">
      <h2>CMA Dishmachines — Ali Group's mid-range value specialist since 2004</h2>
      <p>
        CMA Dishmachines started in Garden Grove, California in the late 1960s — a Southern California original
        that grew into a national commercial dishwasher brand through the 80s and 90s before Ali Group acquired
        it in 2004. Manufacturing has since moved to Ali Group NA's Winston-Salem, North Carolina facility, which
        also serves as CMA's parts supply and corporate home. But the LA installed base dates back to the Garden
        Grove era — 20-to-30-year-old CMA units are still running in long-tenure LA restaurants, and those units
        trace back to the brand's SoCal heritage.
      </p>
      <p>
        What Ali Group brings to CMA is parts discipline and sister-brand service infrastructure. The Winston-Salem
        parts channel that supplies Champion flagship machines also supplies CMA value-tier machines — same service
        account, same parts availability, same Ali Group quality control. That's the practical advantage of a CMA
        purchase over a non-Ali value-tier competitor: you're buying into the broader Ali Group ecosystem.
      </p>
      <p>
        CMA positions below Champion in the Ali Group product hierarchy — mid-range value segment — and well below
        Hobart in the broader commercial dishwasher market. For LA SMB restaurants, independent bars, small catering
        operations, and secondary installs where a premium-tier machine would be over-specified, CMA is typically
        the sensible choice. Repair economics are favorable throughout the first 10–12 years of service, and the
        Ali Group parts chain keeps parts available for 15+ years.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

